    "body": "Any node can be used as the bootstrap node. If you want to instantiate a small network, just start geth on one machine. It will start up and eventually print\n\n``` text\nI0407 20:35:00.226453   16925 udp.go:212] Listening, enode://fe556af88ae0d207972412fd1dc0af356f68f5b0af0a69b5cc17e54c12962988f18034671120c1a0623549f76391f7633183addd97da8c897f073aae0678b44d@92.109.136.143:30303\n```\n\nOn other machines, you can pass the enode URL that it prints to `--bootnodes` and they will all find each other. Note that it sometimes fails to discover its own IP. In that case the URL will have `[::]:30303` at the end. You can just replace the `[::]` with the IP of the machine.\n",
