    "created_at": "2020-04-03T18:31:37Z",
    "updated_at": "2020-04-03T18:31:37Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This is now resolved because we have improved the documentation: https://geth.ethereum.org/docs/interface/private-network explains how to set up a network of multiple nodes where one is the bootnode. cmd/bootnode is officially deprecated.\r\n\r\n@jinfwhuang the network protocol is the same for all nodes, there is no separate protocol for the bootnode. See https://github.com/ethereum/devp2p for networking specifications. \r\n\r\nYou might also be interested in the DNS discovery setup guide, which explains how to set up a DNS-based discovery mechanism for private networks: https://geth.ethereum.org/docs/developers/dns-discovery-setup",
